name: Kidney Transplant Clinic
bio: The kidney transplant clinic is open Monday to Friday from 8:30AM - 4:30PM.

name: Transplant Coordinator On-Call
bio: The transplant coordinator is on-call during evenings and weekends. Please call if you have any emergencies.

name: Marc Melcher
bio: Dr. Melcher serves as an Associate Professor of Surgery at the Stanford University Medical Center. After receiving his BA in biochemistry from Harvard University, he went on to complete his medical doctorate at Columbia University, and a Ph.D. in molecular biology from UC Berkeley. He was formerly the president of the San Francisco Surgical Society. Now, at Stanford, he does research and clinical trials on organ transplantation and is interested in the implementation of AI algorithms in making decisions in transplantation surgery. He practices at Stanford Hospital and Lucile Packard Childrenâ€™s Hospital.

name: Uerica Wang
bio: Uerica Wang, Pharm.D., BCPS received her Doctor of Pharmacy degree and completed a pharmacy practice residency at the University of California, San Francisco. She currently works as a kidney, liver, and intestinal transplant pharmacist at Stanford Health Care.

name: Kabir Jolly
bio: Kabir is a part of the development team for Kidney Care. He is a frosh from The Woodlands, TX interested in AI and app development. Kabir is really excited about the intersection of computer science with healthcare and business, and am currently exploring both of these ideas at Stanford. He loves to play tennis, watch all types of good movies, and spend time with friends.

name: Amrita Kaur
bio: Amrita (she/her) is a part of the development team for Kidney Care. She is a MS student in Computer Science, with a BS in Biology. Amrita isn't sure yet what her future career will look like, but knows that she wants to work on creating a more equitable, just world. She loves watching TV and film (Aziz Ansari's Master of None is a perfect show!) and playing tennis in her free time.

name: Rachel Naidich
bio: Rachel is a part of the development team for Kidney Care. She is a sophomore at Stanford studying computer science, and is passionate about startups and creating technologies that have positive impact. In her free time, Rachel enjoys going for runs and playing chess.
